Git Version Controlling system:
------------------------------

2 VCS:
1. Client-server based VCS
	CVS, SVN
	 - Online
	 - one bigger repo
2. Distributed VCS (DVCS)
	- Offline mode
	- Distributed
	- branching/merging easier
	- one time checkout
 - You cannot download/checkout a single file/dir or branch
 - This is suitable for small code bases
 - make many smaller repo
 
 Git, Mercurial, Bazaar ...
 
 Git:
 -----
 Providers: Bitbucket/Stash (Atlassian), Gitlab, Gitblit Git
	On premises: Your own data center
				
	Cloud based : Github, Bitbucket
 
Git client:  git-scm.com
------------
git-bash on your start menu

$git clone <remote repo URL>
$ cd repo
$git status 
 git add 
 git commit -m""
 git push
 
 steps :
 1. Clone
 2. Create a new file 
 3. git add Hello.txt
 4. git commit -m"my firsyt commit"
 5. git push
 
 
- Like SVN, in git also there is verisoning
	These versions we call as : Sha1sum
	these sha1sums are uniq
git rm, checkout, log, remote add, 

git stash, clean, blame, branch, tags

merging:

be in destination
R1-> master
src -> dest

dest>git merge src
master>git merge R1


Merging:
---------
1. merge  : merge commit 
2. Rebase : there is no merge commit
3. Cherry-pick





